China Should Open Import, Export Policies, Lamy Says

-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 
2011-09-16T02:12:54Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-16/china-should-open-import-export-policies-lamy-says-correct-.html
(Corrects to show that Lamy is not in Beijing)  China  should open its import and
export policies further, according to written remarks that will
be delivered on behalf of World Trade Organization Director
General Pascal Lamy in Beijing today.  The nation needs to reach a better balance between external
and domestic demand, according to the written remarks to be
given at a forum to discuss the 10th anniversary of China’s
entry into the world trade body.  The country faces challenges from an aging population and
environmental problems, according to Lamy’s remarks.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Nerys Avery at 
 navery2@bloomberg.net  